00:00:00,069 --> 00:00:06,393
Also breaking tonight, Medford High School students will have to comply with new security protocols when they go back to class.

2
00:00:06,913 --> 00:00:11,456
The superintendent sent a letter to parents today explaining the extra precautions.

3
00:00:11,976 --> 00:00:14,818
Remember, a student was stabbed in a bathroom earlier this month.

4
00:00:15,578 --> 00:00:20,921
Afterwards, several students complained about a lack of safety on campus and actually staged a walkout.

5
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:27,225
Starting Tuesday, bathrooms will be monitored and will be limited to two students at a time.

6
00:00:27,905 --> 00:00:31,149
Tonight, WBZ reached out to the family of the stabbing victim.

7
00:00:31,189 --> 00:00:32,891
That's 17-year-old Jordan Pineda.

8
00:00:33,512 --> 00:00:37,217
His mother says she does not believe these new measures are going to help.

9
00:00:37,777 --> 00:00:43,865
She also said her son is recovering physically, but will carry the mental trauma forever.

